  "title": "Infant Care Educator (Central and South)",
  "description": "<h2>🏫We are looking for a caring and dedicated Infant Care Teacher to join our centre.👶</h2><p><strong>Working location:</strong> Central and South<br /><strong>Benefits:</strong> AWS/PB and Medical<br /><strong>Working hours:</strong> Rotating (Mon - Fri)<br /><strong>Gross Salary:</strong> Up to $3800 (Basic Salary: Up to $3500)<br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p><ul><li>Provide daily care for infants, including feeding, diapering, and nap routines</li><li>Plan and conduct age-appropriate activities to support infants’ physical, emotional, and cognitive development</li><li>Observe, record, and document infants’ progress and developmental milestones</li><li>Ensure cleanliness, safety, and hygiene of the learning environment in accordance with ECDA guidelines</li><li>Communicate effectively with parents on infants’ care routines and development</li><li>Work closely with colleagues to ensure consistent and quality infant care services<br /></li></ul></p><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><p><ul><li><strong>Diploma or relevant qualification in Infant Care / Early Childhood Care & Education (ACEY, CEC, or equivalent)</strong></li><li><strong>Certified and recognised by ECDA</strong></li><li>Prior experience in infant care is an advantage; fresh graduates are welcome</li><li>Patient, caring, and attentive to the needs of infants</li><li>Good communication and teamwork skills<br /></li></ul><p>Interested applicants can send your latest updated resume to felix@talentsatwork.sg or apply directly through the platform. We will be happy to schedule an exploratory call with you.<br /><br />Talents@Work Pte Ltd (21C0501)<br />Felix Tan Chin Kuang (R25158946)</p></p>",
